10.Name: 2018 DCPC Men's Paddle Championships
10.Details: Welcome and registration at 8:00am for Open Division. Matches start promptly at 8:30. Full 2 out of 3 sets for all rounds. Welcome and registration at 11:30 for Polo Division. 2 out of 3 sets, first to 10-point tie breaker for 3rd.

5.Name: The Ferocious 40s Men's Invitational
5.Details:
This tournament will be hosted at Dedham Country and Polo Club (with matches played at other sites as well).  The draw will be limited to 32 teams.  Every team is guaranteed 3 matches.

To be eligible for this Tournament, Boston League players must have a Player Rating of 42 or higher... and no team can have an average Player Rating below 46.  For non-Boston League players, you should have an APTA rating no greater than 3.0.

Please contact Evan Ambrose at eambrose@dedhamclub.org with any questions.
5.RegistrationDetails: Registration is $125 per team.  Lunch will be served at Dedham, breakfast food will be provided at each hut.
5.Question1: Are you an APTA member?  Please provide your # (can be looked up on www.platformtennis.org)

9.Name: Brae Burn Club Championship
9.Details: This year's Club championship will be run on this site.  We'll limit the field to 12 teams.  Everyone's guaranteed 3 matches.  All matches (including back-draw matches) will count toward your Player Rating
9.RegistrationDetails: The cost of the tourney will be billed to your BBCC monthly statement.

7.Name: Wellesley Weekend Warriors Paddle Tournament
7.Details:
The WWW tournament will be hosted at Wellesley Country club (with matches played at other local clubs as well).  The draw will be limited to 32 teams.  Every team is guaranteed 3 matches.

To be eligible for this tournament, Boston League players must have a Player rating of 34 or higher... and no team may have an average Player Rating below 38.  For non-Boston League players, you should have an APTA rating of 3.5 or below.

Registration is now Open.  Please contact David McNaughton at tennis@wellesleycc.com with any questions.
7.RegistrationDetails: Registration is $125 per team.  Lunch will be served at Wellesley and breakfast food will be available in each hut.
7.Question1: Are you an APTA member?  Please provide your # (can be looked up on www.platformtennis.org)

8.Name: The Squirrel Cup
8.Details:
The Squirrel Cup will be hosted at The Country Club in Brookline (with matches played at other local sites as well). Please prepare yourself for a all day event 8:30am-5pm!! The draw will be limited to 32 teams. Every effort will be made to guarantee each team 3 matches.
To be eligible for the Squirrel Cup, Boston League players must have a Player Rating of 18 or higher... and no team may have an average Player Rating lower than 22. For non-Boston League players, you should have an APTA rating of 4.5 or below.

Looking for a Partner?
You are not alone! Read below for the contact information of players who would also like to play, but don’t have a partner.
Joseph Benevito (josephbenevento@yahoo.com) Rating: 4.5 APTA
8.RegistrationDetails: Registration is $150 per team.  Lunch will be served at TCC.
8.Question1: Are you an APTA member?  Please provide your # (can be looked up on www.platformtennis.org)

2660.Name: The Brookline "B"
2660.Details:
The Brookline "B" will take place on Saturday, November 10th.  The host site will be Brookline Paddle... with matches also taking place at several other nearby clubs.  Each team is guaranteed at least 3 matches.

To be eligible for this tournament, your team must have an average League Rating no better/lower than 30.  Also, no individual with a League Rating below 26 will be eligible (so a 26 would need to partner with a 34+ in order to be eligible).  For those not in the League, you must have an APTA rating no better than 4.0.

Please email Amin at akhadduri@gmail.com with any questions.
2660.RegistrationDetails:
The cost per team for this tourney is $120.  Lunch will be provided at the host site as well as paddle balls, gatorade, water, snacks etc at each of the facilities.

Registration for this tourney makes you a member of the GBPTA

Please email any questions to Amin at akhadduri@gmail.com

2663.Details:

2782.Name: Ferocious Forties PTI 45+
2782.Details:
The 3rd annual Ferocious Forties APTA paddle tournament will be held on Saturday, February 1st at Dedham Country and Polo Club and other surrounding clubs. All players must have a PTI of 45+ and be members of the APTA.

Matches begin at 8:30am on 2/1/20 and play is expected to finish by 4:00pm.

Registration opens on Monday, December 23rd. Please register with a partner at (insert link here).

All teams are guaranteed 3 matches. Players will receive a commemorative favor and prizes will be awarded to main draw champions.

The entry fee is $80 per player.

Email tournament director, Evan Ambrose, at eambrose@dedhamclub.org if you are unsure of your PTI or with any other questions.

Last year's 2019 finalists were Seth McNay & Steven Glick (TCC) and The Champions were Randy Mahoney and Jake Homiller (DCPC).

2784.Name: CANCELED: APTA Men's PTI 20+ Nationals / Squirrel Cup
2784.Details:
APTA Men's PTI 20+ National Championships

(The Squirrel Cup)

Date: 	        Saturday, March 28, 2020

Locations: 	The Squirrel Cup will be hosted at The Country 
                        Club in Brookline, MA (with matches played at 
                        other local sites as well).
 
Please prepare yourself for an all day event 8:30am-8pm!!

Contact: 	Bruno Santarelli   617-456-3954   bsantarelli@tcclub.org

Entry:	APTA Online Entry using the link below

http://www.platformtennis.org/Tournaments/APTA-National-Championships/APTA_PTI_Men_PTI_20__Nationals.htm

Full APTA membership is required for all National Championships.  

Membership may be purchased during tournament entry.

The draw will be limited to 32 teams and we will let teams in, in groups of 4 after 3/9/20 to ensure guaranteed matches etc.. 

Every effort will be made to guarantee each team 3 matches.

All matches will be best of 3 sets with a super tie break and double deuce scoring for the 3rd set except the Main Draw Finals.

Light breakfast, Lunch a favor for each player and beer/prizes!

Details:	

An Individual’s PTI for purposes of registering for a PTI Nationals is deemed to be frozen on the day of registration for the tournament. For example, If you are a 20 when you register for the Men’s PTI 20+ National Championship and subsequently your PTI goes below a 20 you are still eligible to play in the 20+ tournament.

If you do not have a PTI and would like to play in a PTI National Championship, please contact: Amin Khadduri at akhadduri@gmail.com

Three matches guaranteed (weather permitting)

Note: There will be a third set match tiebreaker and double deuce for all draws
 	
Official APTA rules will govern play.
